<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12754] Change cassandra.wait_for_tracing_events_timeout_secs default to -1 so C* doesn&apos;t wait on trace events to be written before responding to request by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12754</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11465&quot; title=&quot;dtest failure in cql_tracing_test.TestCqlTracing.tracing_unknown_impl_test&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11465&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-11465&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; introduces a new system property &lt;tt&gt;cassandra.wait_for_tracing_events_timeout_secs&lt;/tt&gt; that controls whether or not C* waits for events to be written before responding to client.   The current default behavior is to wait up to 1 second and then respond and timeout.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If using probabilistic tracing this can cause queries to be randomly delayed up to 1 second.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Changing the default to -1 (disabled and enabling it explicitly in &lt;tt&gt;cql_tracing_test.TestCqlTracing.tracing_unknown_impl_test&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally it would be nice to be able to control this behavior on a per request basis (which would require native protocol changes).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
